					<p>I am very disappointed in KWTN. Before you find someone guilty in the court of public opinion, you ought to have all the facts. You clearly don’t.<br>
   Did  you find out that the alleged victim had changed her narrative  many times?   There were many versions of her story and none of them made much sense. That her own brother was in the room where and when the violations were to have taken place?<br>
